        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 8 at 11:47AM MDT until August 9 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Temperatures near 100 degrees in the Albuquerque Metro Area.

* WHERE...Middle Rio Grande Valley including the Albuquerque Metro
Area.

* WHEN...For the first Heat Advisory, until 7 PM MDT this evening.
For the second Heat Advisory, from noon to 7 PM MDT Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures may cause heat illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
